parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas tank ventilation system can cause the tank to implode, leading to gas leaks, spills, and potentially a fire hazard due to the proximity of the hot exhaust system.
symptoms: Popping or thumping noises from the gas tank area
difficulty removing the gas cap
air rushing in when the cap is removed
incorrect gas gauge readings
strong gas odor
and gas leaks around the tank seams.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration due to Throttle Cable/Throttle Body Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities, especially when entering highways or merging with traffic.
symptoms: The throttle cable gets stuck
the vehicle continues to accelerate even after letting off the gas pedal
the RPMs rev up to high levels (e.g.
3500 RPMs) without driver input
the vehicle surges forward despite applying the brakes
and the vehicle accelerates rapidly without driver control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty idle speed regulator can cause the engine to surge or rev excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine RPMs rev up to high levels (e.g.
3500 RPMs) without driver input
the vehicle surges forward despite applying the brakes
and the vehicle accelerates rapidly without driver control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to remain running even after the key is removed, leading to potential safety risks, such as unintended acceleration or fire hazards.
symptoms: The engine remains running after the key is removed
the engine will not shut off
the vehicle fails to restart after the engine is shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant leaks, overheating, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
overheating
engine damage
radiator failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's visibility and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The hood suddenly opens while driving
the hood crashes against the windshield
the hood blocks visibility
the hood latch is broken or missing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake warning light switch can lead to inconsistent brake light operation, potentially causing confusion or accidents on the road.
symptoms: The brake warning light remains on or off
even when the brake pedal is not pressed; the warning brake light comes on when the vehicle is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
especially when lifting foot from the brake pedal; the vehicle goes out of control; airbags may fail to deploy in the event of an accident.
